,Not Recommended,568930,35119026,Posted: 21 September,all,fantomchoder,"From what I was able to play... it was awesome. The graphics were fantastic with a good attention to detail to build terrifying environments. The sound quality was excellent and helped create a tense atmosphere. From what I played, the story was simple but made me want to keep playing to find out more. However, this game is a technical mess and I gave up on it despite all that.As others have confirmed, the game will randomly crash for no apparent reason. Luckily my save points weren't affected and it always crashes clean so it was easy to pick back up - but yeah, obviously very annoying regardless.I was going to keep playing despite the crashes, but then I lost my save point. I'm on Win10 playing with a Xbox One controller - and the game handles it fine except for the menus. I noticed when starting a new game that, when it asks you to confirm yes or no to begin, moving the thumbstick left/right to choose yes/no didn't highlight the active choice to show what you're about to select with the gamepad. At the time I just blindly moved the thumbstick left toward yes and pushed A which successfully started my new game. When I was done playing for the time being, I hit start and then moved the thumbstick down until I got to the option for exiting the game (these menu texts highlight correctly). Somehow I ended up being prompted for a new game with the blind yes/no confirmation which confused me since I was certain that I hit the exit game menu option. I again blindly moved the thumbstick right toward no and pushed A - and to my surprise it started a new game which wiped out all my previous progress. This is when I learned two annoyances about the controller support for my setup. The first is that the yes/no confirmations don't let me select no at all... it always selects yes regardless of which direction the thumbstick moves. The second is that I can't use my controller to select the option to exit the game. For some reason it skips over the exit game option and moves back to the first option which happens to be start new game. I realized when I thumbsticked down to the menu option before exit, I hit down and then A very quickly without confirming that exit actually highlighted which then lead me to the confirmation that doesn't let me say no. And there's my lost progress.A few other annoyances were some delays when pressing jump which seemed to be randomly mistimed and poor collision detection with objects. There's some areas where your character tends to get a bit stuck, or an impossible jump that looks easily feasible.Very disappointed that I couldn't finish it."
